text: The PIOH for the SR 138/I-20 is going on now until 8 p.m.pic.twitter.com/UVsI1GJOll – at American Legion Post 77
We appreciate all the hard work our crews have done the last few days. They were incredibly dedicated to getting you home safe! PC: J.Coferpic.twitter.com/YunOqjiyNO
Need info on re-entry? Check here! Also follow our partners. @511Georgia @GeorgiaEMApic.twitter.com/ycEJuAsgOd
Do you need some updates? You can find ALL of them right here. http://ow.ly/hO7p30500Op pic.twitter.com/lwFcSJV9Yp
Did you know that the @511Georgia website and app can give you details on road closures?
We are ready to be out there tomorrow morning to get the roads clear so you can get home. We are putting in a lot of hard work for you, GA!pic.twitter.com/3zOoTdNkZN
The roads are definitely not clear but if anybody can do it, its our crews and partners. @GeorgiaPower @ga_dps @GeorgiaEMApic.twitter.com/BfeJzIFw5Z
From dawn to dusk, we are still hard at work inspecting bridges. Please follow us here for updates. pic.twitter.com/T9WP8cTUtu
For the most up to date information on re-entry, check here! http://ow.ly/56aN304ZfW7 http://ow.ly/XpVV304ZfFJ
We need you to have patience in clearing the roads. We want you to go home but we want you to arrive unharmed. We will update you ASAP.pic.twitter.com/4wJIVzyTOM
For the most up to date information on re-entry, check here! http://ow.ly/XpVV304ZfFJ
Please WAIT to re-enter the coastal areas. We need to be able to get to our sites along with emergency personnel.pic.twitter.com/Ooex0BHCUz
100s of GDOT employees are here for you either on the roads or at offices. No matter the hour, send us a question and we will get to you.pic.twitter.com/zsbWhZ60B9
We will let you know immediately when roads are open after storm damages are accessed. @GeorgiaEMApic.twitter.com/Y9aY3P4XcI
You may drive a large truck or SUV but it only takes a few inches to carry it away. Do not underestimate flood waters. #HurricaneMatthewpic.twitter.com/rSkNFi1M18
Hurricanes can produce deadly flooding hundreds of miles inland. Prepare: http://ow.ly/Ndcg304Yu28 pic.twitter.com/FfcY8BHvUm
If you must drive, don't pass barricades and do not move through rising water. Your car may get stuck or be swept away.pic.twitter.com/TMxl3Vx8mT
Need to report an outage? Do so here with our friends at @GeorgiaPower Georgia Power http://ow.ly/Emly304YuPB
High winds will be prevalent tonight at above 70 mph with Flash Flood Watches and Warnings affecting multiple counties.
With the heavy rain coming in, you need these facts. Don’t pass a barricade and be careful of raised waters.pic.twitter.com/4o3bcF6C0m
Beginning at 12:30 today contraflow will be disengaged. I-16 eastbound at US 301/Exit 116 to Savannah will remain closed.pic.twitter.com/sppy6qHgtX
